'''Pascal Touzeau''' (born 1969) is a French dancer and choreographer of [[contemporary dance]].
Touzeau studied dance at the [[conservatoire de Bordeaux]]. A professional dancer since 1987, he started as a dancer at the {{ill|Opéra national de Bordeaux|fr}}, then Bonn, Wiesbaden and finally the {{ill|Ballet de Francfort|fr}} directed by [[William Forsythe (choreographer)|William Forsythe]]. Touzeau became choreographer in Germany, France, Sweden and the Netherlands before being appointed head of the [[Madrid Ballet|Ballet Carmen Roche]]<ref>[http://balletcarmenroche.com/ Ballet Carmen Roche]</ref> in Madrid (2005 to 2006).
Touzeau has been director of the [[Staatstheater Mainz]] since 2009.
